ption><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/vytEK6Z.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Over the past 10,000 years, evolution in West Eurasia has been selecting for light skin, red hair and resistance to HIV and leprosy in humans, according to a new study.

